CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1953, pg. 36, reads: "The JWJ's Open House - Last Sunday, Oct. 11, found Pittsburghers wending their way to the open house - house warming given by the John Wesley Johnsons in their new home at 3510 Iowa Street. Pittsburghers all were invited through Toki's column.  Pictured during the hours of three to five were, left photo, Mrs. Robert Ratcliffe, John Geisler, Johnny Johnson, the host; Mrs. Alma Illery and Mrs. Carroll Holmes... - Teenie Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Robert Ratcliffe, John Geisler, John Wesley Johnson, Alma Illery, and Mrs. Carroll Holmes, standing in front of fireplace in Johnson home, 3510 Iowa Street, Upper Hill District
